From Document 1:
- The client application sends messages containing user input
- The client application recognizes client actions in responses
- The client application executes the action (e.g., calling an external service)
- The client application stores the result in the specified context variable
- The client application sends a message back to the service with the updated context
- A child node handles the response from the client action

The JSON example shows:
```json
{
  "actions": [
    {
      "name": "get_weather",
      "type": "client",
      "parameters": {
        "location": "$location"
      },
      "result_variable": "weather_forecast"
    }
  ]
}
```

And the child node would handle the result:
```json
{
  "output": {
    "text": {
      "values": [
        "It will be $weather_forecast in $location.literal today."
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

